Australian coronavirus contact tracing app voluntary and with 'no hidden agenda', minister says Read moreIn Australia, contact tracing is typically used to monitor the transmission of illnesses such as the measles.
Photograph: Darren England/AAPFor now, the work of contact tracing is conducted by teams working within state public health units.
The team includes a communicable diseases manager, surveillance nurses, public health nurses and public health officers.
Dr Shopna BagCase investigation and contact tracing work begins at the point of diagnosis.
“Sometimes people are expecting the result, other times it’s a surprise,” says Dr Bhakti Vasant, a public health physician in Brisbane’s metro south public health unit.